\par 
\par }\pard \qj\fi-2880\li2880\nowidctlpar\tx-720\tx0\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\hyphpar0\adjustright {\f0\expnd0\expndtw-3\lang3081 Critical Path:\tab \tab \tab The longest sequential path of activities in a project which connects the beginning and the end of a project. The sum total of the activity durations along this path is equal to the minimum project duration. The critical path is shown by a heavy arrow, and is where the earliest start time equals the latest start time, and the earliest finish time equals the latest finish time.
\par }\pard \qj\nowidctlpar\tx-720\hyphpar0\adjustright {\f0\expnd0\expndtw-3\lang3081 
\par 
\par 
\par 
\par }\pard \qj\fi-2880\li2880\nowidctlpar\tx-720\tx0\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\hyphpar0\adjustright {\f0\expnd0\expndtw-3\lang3081 Earliest Event Time:\tab \tab The earliest possible time at which all activities terminating at the event can be completed. Indicated in a square at the head of one activity arrow terminating at this event.
