\par }{\i\f0\expnd0\expndtw-3\lang3081 Event or Node Numbering}{\f0\expnd0\expndtw-3\lang3081 
\par 
\par Events or Nodes are identified by numbers.  The term event does not necessarily mean that something accomplished at a node it represents, only a point in time at which an activity arrow originates or terminates.  There is not a rigid rule in numbering events or nodes but the preceding node or nodes should be smaller than that node at which the activity arrow(s) enter.  When the initial network planning phase is established the network should then be numbered.  It can be prudent to number the network only with even or odd numbers because this provides numbers for unforeseen future addition of activities.  (See Fig. 10.5).
